<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="107" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,474,825]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,546,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species related to 
<emphasis box="[538,756,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malski" authorityYear="1962" box="[538,752,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paralobi">Cheilosia paralobi</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but differs in the following characters: face partly microtrichose on genae, along paraface and between antennae and facial tubercle in 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[1019,1142,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candida" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1019,1142,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. candida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1151,1216,583,609]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1151,1216,583,609]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1232,1322,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[164,1411,205,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[164,1424,181,1936]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A, C, D male of Cheilosia candida sp. n. B, E male of Cheilosia paralobi. A, B head, lateral view, C head, dorsal view, D, E antennae, lateral view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402962/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malski" authorityYear="1962" box="[151,281,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paralobi">
<emphasis box="[151,281,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. paralobi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
entire face microtrichose, except facial tubercle (
<figureCitation box="[844,931,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[164,1411,205,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[164,1424,181,1936]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A, C, D male of Cheilosia candida sp. n. B, E male of Cheilosia paralobi. A, B head, lateral view, C head, dorsal view, D, E antennae, lateral view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402962/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); basoflagellomere of male partly reddish in 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,274,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candida" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[151,274,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. candida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[282,346,655,681]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[282,346,655,681]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[361,449,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[164,1411,205,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[164,1424,181,1936]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A, C, D male of Cheilosia candida sp. n. B, E male of Cheilosia paralobi. A, B head, lateral view, C head, dorsal view, D, E antennae, lateral view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402962/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malski" authorityYear="1962" box="[570,699,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paralobi">
<emphasis box="[570,699,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. paralobi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
almost completely black (
<figureCitation box="[997,1081,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[164,1411,205,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[164,1424,181,1936]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A, C, D male of Cheilosia candida sp. n. B, E male of Cheilosia paralobi. A, B head, lateral view, C head, dorsal view, D, E antennae, lateral view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402962/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
) (in some specimens inner side basally with paler macula); frons covered with intermixed black and yellow pile in 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[1099,1222,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candida" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1099,1222,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. candida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1231,1295,691,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1231,1295,691,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malski" authorityYear="1962" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paralobi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. paralobi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only with yellow pile. Male genitalia: surstylus shorter in 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[903,1026,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candida" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[903,1026,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. candida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1033,1096,727,753]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1033,1096,727,753]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, about three times longer than broad basally (
<figureCitation box="[317,405,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[155,1434,937,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-1497@6.[151,1436,931,1704]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genitalia of Cheilosia candida sp. n., lateral view. A male genitalia without surstylus B surstylus. ep—epandrium, hp—hypandrium, ce—cercus, godl—dorsal lobus of gonostylus, arrow pointed dorsal prolongation on godl, govl—ventral lobus of gonostylus. Scale bar, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402968/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malski" authorityYear="1962" box="[524,653,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paralobi">
<emphasis box="[524,653,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. paralobi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
very narrow apically and elongated, more than five times longer than broad basally (
<figureCitation box="[317,403,798,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[168,1407,185,1873]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[151,1436,181,1889]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. A–D Epandrium of male genitalia, lateral view, E Surstylus of male genitalia in Cheilosia paralobi, lateral view.A Cheilosia cumanica, B Cheilosia hypena, C Cheilosia laticornis, D Cheilosia sulcifrons. ep—epandrium, sst—surstylus. Scale bar, 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402970" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402970/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402964" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4402964" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402964/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" startId="4.[151,250,1315,1339]" targetBox="[157,1431,854,1284]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1315,1375]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1315,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Gonostylus of male genitalia, lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[737,754,1315,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">A</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1857" box="[763,962,1315,1339]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifacies">
<emphasis box="[763,962,1315,1339]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Cheilosia latifacies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[977,994,1315,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">B</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Becker" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[1003,1182,1315,1339]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypena">
<emphasis box="[1003,1182,1315,1339]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">Cheilosia hypena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1198,1216,1315,1339]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[1225,1437,1315,1339]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Szilady" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[1225,1433,1315,1339]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cumanica">Cheilosia cumanica</taxonomicName>
